JOHNSON Date: NOV 12,1996 EC Decision Jan-16.1997 On AUG 14, 1996 you appeared for an examination on your application for naturalization, and on OCT 16, 1996 you failed to appear for reexamination. Pursuant to the investigation and examination on your application, it is determined that you are ineligible for naturalization. Section 312 of the Immigration and Nationality Act, 8 USC 1423, provides in pertinent part that "[no] person except as otherwise provided shall hereafter be naturalized who cannot demonstrate an understanding of the English language, including an ability to read, write and speak wording in ordinary usage in the English language [and] a knowledge and understanding of the fundamentals of the history, and of the principles and form of government, of the United States. You have failed to meet the requirements of Section 312 in that: [X] You have failed to demonstrate ability to speak and understand the English language sufficiently to answer the questions in your interview and on your application, and are not exempt from the requirement. [X] You have failed to demonstrate ability to write words in ordinary usage in the English language which were presented to you to write, and are not exempt from the requirement. P 321 616 767 [X] You have failed to demonstrated knowledge of the hists and form of government, of the United States.
